The paper deals with an information-theoretic analysis of data deduplication, which involves source coding techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses fixed and variable-length deduplication schemes, which are related to data structures and algorithms, indicating that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions the importance of boundary synchronization, which is related to security and cryptography, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the practical importance of deduplication in cloud and enterprise server settings, indicating that it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
